subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 88
). Socii weakly developed; valva large with small neck and very short ventral incision; sacculus somewhat convex postmedially; cucullus very large, oval; aedeagus broad basally, slender in postmedian half, with dorsoterminal hook; henion well sclerotized, without thorns.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 115
). Papilla analis small; apophyses moderate, slender; proximal part of sterigma tapered anteriorly, postostial part about twice longer, well sclerotized posteriorly; sclerite of cingulum small, subterminal; one pair of strong signa.
